import React, { useState } from 'react' import axios from 'axios'; const URI="localhost:4000" const Register = () => { const[values,setValues]=useState({uname:"",email:"",password:"",jobTitle:"",hireDate:Date,department:"",contact:"" }) const changeHandler=(event)=>{ const {name,value}=event.target; setValues({...values,[name]:value}) } const submitHandler=async(event)=>{ event.preventDefault(); await axios.post(URI+"/register",values) console.log(values); } return (
Register
{changeHandler}
) } export default Register
